claim.claim-text:
A resonant power conversion apparatus comprising:
a power source (110) configured to supply power;
a capacitor (120) connected in parallel to the power source (110), the capacitor (120) is configured to be charged with the power from the power source (110);
a discharge circuit (130) connected in parallel to the capacitor (120), and including a resistor (132) and a switch (134) connected in series, the discharge circuit (130) is configured to discharge the capacitor (130) before the power is supplied from the power source (110) to a load (150); and
a switch control circuit (140) configured to provide a switch control signal to the switch (134) to control a discharge time point and a discharge period of the discharge circuit (130).

A method of operating a resonant power conversion apparatus, the method comprising:
charging a capacitor (120), connected in parallel to a power source (110), with power supplied from the power source (110);
determining a discharge time point and a discharge period of a discharge circuit (130), the discharge circuit (130) including a resistor (132) and a switch (134) connected in series, and the discharge circuit (130) is connected in parallel to the capacitor (120);
providing, by a switch control circuit (140), a switch control signal determined based on the discharge time point and the discharge period; and
discharging the charged capacitor (120) through the resistor (132) based on the switch control signal applied to the switch (134).
